WHO   — DODGEBALL — a film-world — the underdog comedy
WHAT  — DodgeBall — the perfect underdog-sports comedy: Average Joe's vs Globo Gym, a wrench-throwing legend of a coach, a man who thinks he's a pirate, two oblivious commentators on ESPN8 'The Ocho,' and the five D's.
WHERE — Average Joe's Gym, a haven of misfits about to be foreclosed by the corporate Globo Gym — until they enter a Las Vegas dodgeball tournament for the prize that saves them  Framework inputs: Peter La Fleur; White Goodman; Patches; Average Joe's; Globo Gym; the five D's  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Universe David 0)
WHY   — A band of lovable misfits learns to dodge a wrench, enters a televised tournament against a corporate gym of athletes, and wins back their home by refusing to be anything but underdogs.
HOW   — Crystallized from DodgeBall: A True Underdog Story (20th Century Fox, 2004).

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Be the misfits no one bets on, take the wrench to the face until you can dodge it, and win your home back on the floor of ESPN8 'The Ocho.'

